Fix social login using wrong client_id in multi-store setups (NKD-6115).

The button URL is built with the default store's base URL. When a user on a
non-default store (e.g. AT) clicks a social login button, the InitOauth request
may run in the default store context (e.g. DE). Account._construct() then reads
the default store's application_id instead of the user's actual store's client_id.

Switching the store to current_store_id before the URL resolver is called ensures
the Account model is instantiated with the correct store-scoped application_id.

diff --git a/Controller/Modal/InitOauth.php b/Controller/Modal/InitOauth.php
--- a/Controller/Modal/InitOauth.php
+++ b/Controller/Modal/InitOauth.php
@@ -177,6 +177,13 @@ class InitOauth implements ActionInterface
             $this->apiCallParamsPersistor->add('referer_url', $this->lastViewedPageProvider->getUrl());
             $this->apiCallParamsPersistor->addQuoteId((int) $this->checkoutSession->getQuoteId());

+            // BEGIN PATCH
+            $currentStoreId = (int) $this->request->getParam('current_store_id');
+            if ($currentStoreId) {
+                $this->storeManager->setCurrentStore($currentStoreId);
+            }
+            // END PATCH
+
             $modalUrl = $this->modalUrlResolverFactory->create($networkCode)->getUrl();
             return $redirectResult->setUrl($modalUrl);
         } catch (NetworkIsNotConfiguredException|NoSuchEntityException $exception) {
